-of-the-year-2018%3Futm_source%3Donsite-share%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3Donsite-share%26utm_brand%3Dbon-appetit&quot;}" href="mailto:?subject=Portland%2C%20Maine%2C%20Is%20the%202018%20Restaurant%20City%20of%20the%20Year&amp;body=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bonappetit.com%2Fstory%2Fportland-maine-city-of-the-year-2018%3Futm_source%3Donsite-share%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3Donsite-share%26utm_brand%3Dbon-appetit" rel=" noopener" target="_blank"><div class="SocialIconContainer-huXzUC pMzVC social-icons__icon-container"><svg class="SocialIconNetworkIconComponent-cZaKGz dlOAhZ icon icon-email" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 32 32" width="32" height="32" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><title>Email</title><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M27.44 7.5H4.56L16 18.94 27.44 7.5ZM3.5 8.56V24.5h25V8.56L16 21.06 3.5 8.56ZM2 26V6h28v20H2Z" fill="#000"></path></svg></div></a></li></ul></div></div><div class="StickyBoxPlaceholder-grPmrg dxAvXx"></div></div></aside></header></div><div data-attribute-verso-pattern="article-body" class="ArticlePageContentBackGround-cNiFNN kAwnHf article-body__content"><div class="ArticlePageChunksContent-etcMtP bwyLBj"><div data-testid="ArticlePageChunks" class="ArticlePageChunks-fLyCVG eOdfIs"><div class="GridWrapper-cAzTTK kHBDeH grid grid-margins grid-items-2 ArticlePageChunksGrid-hfxaau eSqXkM grid-layout--adrail narrow wide-adrail"><div class="GridItem-buujkM stRKV grid--item grid-layout__content"><div class="BodyWrapper-kufPGa jVpVTh body body__container article__body" data-journey-hook="client-content" data-testid="BodyWrapper"><div class="body__inner-container"><p><strong>Full disclosure: I’ve got a thing for Maine.</strong> I went to college there, I got married there, I regularly vacation there. And I’ve always believed that Portland has one of the more vibrant, compelling food scenes, thanks in no small part to all that pristine seafood and craft beer. I’ve written about the Forest City (who knew it was called that?) and its restaurants more than any other city besides New York. I even called it <a href="https://www.bonappetit.com/columns/the-foodist/article/portland-maine-america-s-foodiest-small-town-2009">America’s Foodiest Small Town</a> in a 2009 story (wow, that title didn’t age well). So, why should you believe me when I declare Portland our 2018 City of the Year? And after years of me talking about it, why now?</p><p>For starters, it’s the sheer number of outstanding openings—from a tiny pastry shop that serves knockout Roman pizza to a Jewish-style deli that ranks up there with New York and L.A.’s best. And while you can still get an Instagram-worthy lobster roll and a dozen local oysters, you’re missing out if you skip the killer pho spot or the guy selling hand rolls out of a Yeti cooler.</p><p>No, this year’s award isn’t a case blind favoritism. It’s simply because this always-tasty city has never tasted better. Want more proof? Here are 20 ways to binge your way through it right now.</p><div><div class="ConsumerMarketingUnitThemedWrapper-iUTMTf jssHut consumer-marketing-unit consumer-marketing-unit--article-mid-content" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true"><div class="consumer-marketing-unit__slot consumer-marketing-unit__slot--article-mid-content consumer-marketing-unit__slot--in-content"></div><div class="journey-unit"></div></div></div><ol><li><p>Start every day with a trip to <a data-offer-url="https://www.tandemcoffee.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.tandemcoffee.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.tandemcoffee.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Tandem Bakery</a>. I find it almost impossible to order anything other than a biscuit slathered in butter and blueberry jam. Wait, I mean the sticky bun. No, the black sesame and banana tea cake. Then again, pretty much everything baker Briana Holt whips up is brilliant.</p></li><li><p>Get a glass of on-tap Maine-made pét-nat <a data-offer-url="http://www.oysterriverwine.com/wines/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;http://www.oysterriverwine.com/wines/&quot;}" href="http://www.oysterriverwine.com/wines/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Morphos</a>, throw back expertly shucked oysters and baby scallops (when in season), and you could easily spend your entire afternoon at <a data-offer-url="http://portland.islandcreekoysters.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;http://portland.islandcreekoysters.com/&quot;}" href="http://portland.islandcreekoysters.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">The Shop at Island Creek Oysters</a>.</p></li><li><p>Treat the high-energy <a data-offer-url="http://www.izakayaminato.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;http://www.izakayaminato.com/&quot;}" href="http://www.izakayaminato.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Izakaya Minato</a> like a sushi bar: Sit at the low-slung kitchen counter and ask chef-owner Thomas Takashi Cooke to give you whatever was swimming nearby yesterday (mackerel, uni, scallops). And when you’ve polished that off, order another glass of sake and a couple plates of JFC (Japanese fried chicken).</p></li></ol></div></div></div><div class="GridItem-buujkM fVLMby grid--item grid-layout__aside"><div class="StickyBoxWrapper-jfYBuk kNleGZ sticky-box"><div class="StickyBoxPrimary-dzWDWL cdhYoN sticky-box__primary"><div class="Container-bkChBi byNLHx"></div><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--rail"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--rail" data-node-id="ka5ey7"></div></div><div class="ConsumerMarketingUnitThemedWrapper-iUTMTf jssHut consumer-marketing-unit consumer-marketing-unit--display-rail" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true"><div class="consumer-marketing-unit__slot consumer-marketing-unit__slot--display-rail"></div><div class="journey-unit"></div></div></div><div class="StickyBoxPlaceholder-grPmrg dxAvXx"></div></div></div></div><div data-testid="RowWrapper" class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd RowWrapper-UmqTg iUEiRd HEhan full-bleed-ad row-mid-content-ad"><div class="StickyMidContentAdWrapper-fSBzwl drzyIa ad-stickymidcontent"><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--mid-content should-hold-space"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--mid-content" data-node-id="1a0z1k"></div></div></div></div><div class="GridWrapper-cAzTTK kHBDeH grid grid-margins grid-items-2 ArticlePageChunksGrid-hfxaau eSqXkM grid-layout--adrail narrow wide-adrail"><div class="GridItem-buujkM stRKV grid--item grid-layout__content"><div class="BodyWrapper-kufPGa jVpVTh body body__container article__body" data-journey-hook="client-content" data-testid="BodyWrapper"><div class="body__inner-container"><figure class="AssetEmbedWrapper-eVDQiB byBkf asset-embed"><div class="AssetEmbedAssetContainer-eJxoAx dBHGoQ asset-embed__asset-container"><span class="SpanWrapper-umhxW kGxnNB responsive-asset AssetEmbedResponsiveAsset-cXBNxi eCxVQK asset-embed__responsive-asset"><picture class="ResponsiveImagePicture-cWuUZO dUOtEa AssetEmbedResponsiveAsset-cXBNxi eCxVQK asset-embed__responsive-asset responsive-image"><noscript><img alt="Image may contain Animal Sea Life Invertebrate Seashell Food Oyster and Clam" class="ResponsiveImageContainer-eybHBd fptoWY responsive-image__image" src="https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_1600%2Cc_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg" srcSet="https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_120,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 120w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_240,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 240w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_320,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 320w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_640,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 640w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_960,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 960w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_1280,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 1280w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_1600,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 1600w" sizes="100vw"/></noscript></picture></span></div><div class="CaptionWrapper-jSZdqE ebtvos caption AssetEmbedCaption-fNQBPI fmQnYP asset-embed__caption"><span class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ CaptionText-bHjzlu iUEiRd fSbQGS iXWezO caption__text"><p>Oysters, pét-nat, repeat at The Shop at Island Creek Oysters</p>
</span><span class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ CaptionCredit-ejegDm iUEiRd eDVoPq fNaHcW caption__credit">Greta Rybus</span></div></figure><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--in-content"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--in-content" data-node-id="ja040l"></div></div><ol start="4"><li><p>Stay at the 15-room <a data-offer-url="https://thefrancismaine.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://thefrancismaine.com/&quot;}" href="https://thefrancismaine.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Francis Hotel</a> set in a historic Victorian Mansion (I prefer the junior suite, room 303). At night I like to sip an old-fashioned in front of the fireplace, but the best reason to stay here might be the fact that it’s located directly across the street from Tandem Bakery (see No. 1).</p></li><li><p>Forget trendy and head to <a data-offer-url="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Ruskis-Tavern/115551755131665" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.facebook.com/pages/Ruskis-Tavern/115551755131665&quot;}" href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Ruskis-Tavern/115551755131665" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Ruski’s Tavern</a>, a neighborhood bar that is open from 7 a.m. (9 a.m. on Sundays) and serves just about every bar food you can imagine. The chili cheese dog will not disappoint. If this place ever dies, so too will Portland.</p></li><li><p>Hit up the Jewish deli that’s worth its weight in legit bagels: <a data-offer-url="https://www.rosefoods.me/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.rosefoods.me/&quot;}" href="https://www.rosefoods.me/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Rose Foods</a>. Yes, I just said that (it&#x27;s on our <a href="https://www.bonappetit.com/story/top-50-best-new-restaurants-2018">Top 50</a> list!). And after you’ve loaded up on perfect Montreal-style bagels, crispy latkes, and a big bowl of matzo ball soup, be sure to purchase one of their soon-to-be-famous canvas totes.</p></li></ol></div></div></div><div class="GridItem-buujkM fVLMby grid--item grid-layout__aside"><div class="StickyBoxWrapper-jfYBuk jxBcTH sticky-box"><div class="StickyBoxPrimary-dzWDWL cdhYoN sticky-box__primary"><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--rail"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--rail" data-node-id="q73h4p"></div></div><div class="ConsumerMarketingUnitThemedWrapper-iUTMTf jssHut consumer-marketing-unit consumer-marketing-unit--display-rail" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true"><div class="consumer-marketing-unit__slot consumer-marketing-unit__slot--display-rail"></div><div class="journey-unit"></div></div><div data-attr-viewport-monitor="" class="RecircMostPopularWrapper-bRuGTi nZGkR recirc-most-popular-wrapper viewport-monitor-anchor"></div></div><div class="StickyBoxPlaceholder-grPmrg dxAvXx"></div></div></div></div><div data-testid="RowWrapper" class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd RowWrapper-UmqTg iUEiRd HEhan full-bleed-ad row-mid-content-ad"><div class="StickyMidContentAdWrapper-fSBzwl drzyIa ad-stickymidcontent"><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--mid-content should-hold-space"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--mid-content" data-node-id="np9hlp"></div></div></div></div><div class="GridWrapper-cAzTTK kHBDeH grid grid-margins grid-items-2 ArticlePageChunksGrid-hfxaau eSqXkM grid-layout--adrail narrow wide-adrail"><div class="GridItem-buujkM stRKV grid--item grid-layout__content"><div class="BodyWrapper-kufPGa jVpVTh body body__container article__body" data-journey-hook="client-content" data-testid="BodyWrapper"><div class="body__inner-container"><figure class="AssetEmbedWrapper-eVDQiB byBkf asset-embed"><div class="AssetEmbedAssetContainer-eJxoAx dBHGoQ asset-embed__asset-container"><span class="SpanWrapper-umhxW kGxnNB responsive-asset AssetEmbedResponsiveAsset-cXBNxi eCxVQK asset-embed__responsive-asset"><picture class="ResponsiveImagePicture-cWuUZO dUOtEa AssetEmbedResponsiveAsset-cXBNxi eCxVQK asset-embed__responsive-asset responsive-image"><noscript><img alt="This image may contain Dish Food Meal and Plant" class="ResponsiveImageContainer-eybHBd fptoWY responsive-image__image" src="https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_1600%2Cc_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg" srcSet="https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_120,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 120w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_240,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 240w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_320,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 320w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_640,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 640w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_960,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 960w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_1280,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 1280w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_1600,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 1600w" sizes="100vw"/></noscript></picture></span></div><div class="CaptionWrapper-jSZdqE ebtvos caption AssetEmbedCaption-fNQBPI fmQnYP asset-embed__caption"><span class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ CaptionText-bHjzlu iUEiRd fSbQGS iXWezO caption__text"><p>Rose Foods brings new meaning to &quot;power breakfast.&quot;</p>
</span><span class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ CaptionCredit-ejegDm iUEiRd eDVoPq fNaHcW caption__credit">Elizabeth Cecil</span></div></figure><ol start="7"><li><p>Order the funky, fresh pho ga at <a data-offer-url="http://congtubot.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;http://congtubot.com/&quot;}" href="http://congtubot.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Cong Tu Bot</a> on Portland’s restaurant row, Washington Avenue. Actually, everything I tried at Vien Dobui and Jessica Sheahan’s lively Vietnamese street food spot was brimming with herbs, heat, and soul.</p></li><li><p>Try your best not to fill up on the standout small plates (see: house-made morcilla, cured local bluefish on smoked onions) at Spanish-leaning <a data-offer-url="https://www.chavalmaine.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.chavalmaine.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.chavalmaine.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Chaval</a>, or you’ll risk being too full to try Ilma Lopez’s desserts. She’s one of the most talented pastry chefs in town, just as skilled with the simple (sticky and addictive maple pie) as the ornate (Paris-Brest with cacao sorbet).</p></li><li><p>Swing by <a data-offer-url="https://www.littlegiantmaine.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.littlegiantmaine.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.littlegiantmaine.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Little Giant</a>, the sophomore effort from the team behind local favorite <a data-offer-url="https://www.huntandalpineclub.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.huntandalpineclub.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.huntandalpineclub.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Portland Hunt + Alpine Club</a>, which gets clever with dishes like lobster chips with serrano ranch and Moxie-braised pork belly. The sister market next door sells local beers and groceries and daily specials (don’t miss Friday and Saturday’s roast chicken and biscuits).</p></li></ol></div></div></div><div class="GridItem-buujkM fVLMby grid--item grid-layout__aside"><div class="StickyBoxWrapper-jfYBuk jxBcTH sticky-box"><div class="StickyBoxPrimary-dzWDWL cdhYoN sticky-box__primary"><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--rail"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--rail" data-node-id="sngd9"></div></div><div class="ConsumerMarketingUnitThemedWrapper-iUTMTf jssHut consumer-marketing-unit consumer-marketing-unit--display-rail" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true"><div class="consumer-marketing-unit__slot consumer-marketing-unit__slot--display-rail"></div><div class="journey-unit"></div></div><div data-attr-viewport-monitor="" class="RecircMostPopularWrapper-bRuGTi nZGkR recirc-most-popular-wrapper viewport-monitor-anchor"></div></div><div class="StickyBoxPlaceholder-grPmrg dxAvXx"></div></div></div></div><div data-testid="RowWrapper" class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd RowWrapper-UmqTg iUEiRd HEhan full-bleed-ad row-mid-content-ad"><div class="StickyMidContentAdWrapper-fSBzwl drzyIa ad-stickymidcontent"><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--mid-content should-hold-space"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--mid-content" data-node-id="ksgzt2"></div></div></div></div><div class="GridWrapper-cAzTTK kHBDeH grid grid-margins grid-items-2 ArticlePageChunksGrid-hfxaau eSqXkM grid-layout--adrail narrow wide-adrail"><div class="GridItem-buujkM stRKV grid--item grid-layout__content"><div class="BodyWrapper-kufPGa jVpVTh body body__container article__body" data-journey-hook="client-content" data-testid="BodyWrapper"><div class="body__inner-container"><figure class="AssetEmbedWrapper-eVDQiB byBkf asset-embed"><div class="AssetEmbedAssetContainer-eJxoAx dBHGoQ asset-embed__asset-container"><span class="SpanWrapper-umhxW kGxnNB responsive-asset AssetEmbedResponsiveAsset-cXBNxi eCxVQK asset-embed__responsive-asset"><picture class="ResponsiveImagePicture-cWuUZO dUOtEa AssetEmbedResponsiveAsset-cXBNxi eCxVQK asset-embed__responsive-asset responsive-image"><noscript><img alt="Image may contain Food Dish Meal Plant Bowl Produce and Vegetable" class="ResponsiveImageContainer-eybHBd fptoWY responsive-image__image" src="https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_1600%2Cc_limit/BA090118portland06.png" srcSet="https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_120,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png 120w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_240,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png 240w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_320,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png 320w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_640,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png 640w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_960,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png 960w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_1280,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png 1280w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_1600,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png 1600w" sizes="100vw"/></noscript></picture></span></div><div class="CaptionWrapper-jSZdqE ebtvos caption AssetEmbedCaption-fNQBPI fmQnYP asset-embed__caption"><span class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ CaptionText-bHjzlu iUEiRd fSbQGS iXWezO caption__text"><p>You need these turmeric-and-lemongrass-laced curry noodles at Cong Tu Bot.</p>
</span><span class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ CaptionCredit-ejegDm iUEiRd eDVoPq fNaHcW caption__credit">Elizabeth Cecil</span></div></figure><ol start="10"><li><p>Visit the wine bar of my dreams: <a data-offer-url="http://www.drifterswife.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;http://www.drifterswife.com/&quot;}" href="http://www.drifterswife.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Drifters Wife</a> (another <a href="https://www.bonappetit.com/story/top-50-best-new-restaurants-2018">Top 50</a> nominee!). Basically, I want the life of owners Peter and Orenda Hale. They’re constantly popping open bottles of chuggable <a href="https://www.bonappetit.com/story/what-is-natural-wine">natural wines</a> from their wine shop and then skipping over to the dining room to feast on mussel toast with nduja and other seasonal plates from chef Ben Jackson. At least this is how I want to believe they live.</p></li><li><p>Follow <a data-offer-url="https://www.facebook.com/mr.tunamaine/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.facebook.com/mr.tunamaine/&quot;}" href="https://www.facebook.com/mr.tunamaine/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Mr. Tuna</a> (a.k.a. Jordan Rubin) and his Japanese-style temaki hand rolls to whatever location he’s popping up at that day. Equipped with only a rice warmer, two Yeti coolers packed with his <em>mise en place</em>, and a cutting board, Rubin frequents breweries and special events serving impeccably fresh seafood. The spicy scallops and crab roll is a bar snack par excellence, but it’s the crab with yuzu mayo and avocado that convinced me to buy a Mr. Tuna T-shirt. I’ve got no problem being a walking advertisement for the guy.</p></li><li><p>Learn why beer geeks get giddy about Portland. Every single day a new brewery opens somewhere in Maine. I’m kidding, kinda. My favorites (with tasting rooms, of course) include groundbreaking <a data-offer-url="https://www.allagash.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.allagash.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.allagash.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Allagash</a>, <a data-offer-url="https://www.bissellbrothers.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.bissellbrothers.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.bissellbrothers.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Bissell Brothers</a>, <a data-offer-url="https://oxbowbeer.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://oxbowbeer.com/&quot;}" href="https://oxbowbeer.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Oxbow</a>, and <a data-offer-url="http://foundationbrew.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;http://foundationbrew.com/&quot;}" href="http://foundationbrew.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Foundation</a>, but newcomer <a data-offer-url="http://www.austinstreetbrewery.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;http://www.austinstreetbrewery.com/&quot;}" href="http://www.austinstreetbrewery.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Austin Street Brewery</a> is getting the buzz of late.</p></li><li><p>Explore the <a data-offer-url="https://www.publicmarkethouse.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.publicmarkethouse.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.publicmarkethouse.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Public Market House</a>—part mall food court, part restaurant incubator. The gem of the bi-level space is <a data-offer-url="https://www.maizportland.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.maizportland.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.maizportland.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Maiz</a>, which serves arepas sliced open like a pita and stuffed with ingredients like chorizo, avocado, and zingy chimichurri sauce.</p></li></ol></div></div></div><div class="GridItem-buujkM fVLMby grid--item grid-layout__aside"><div class="StickyBoxWrapper-jfYBuk jxBcTH sticky-box"><div class="StickyBoxPrimary-dzWDWL cdhYoN sticky-box__primary"><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--rail"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--rail" data-node-id="iacvpr"></div></div><div class="ConsumerMarketingUnitThemedWrapper-iUTMTf jssHut consumer-marketing-unit consumer-marketing-unit--display-rail" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true"><div class="consumer-marketing-unit__slot consumer-marketing-unit__slot--display-rail"></div><div class="journey-unit"></div></div><div data-attr-viewport-monitor="" class="RecircMostPopularWrapper-bRuGTi nZGkR recirc-most-popular-wrapper viewport-monitor-anchor"></div></div><div class="StickyBoxPlaceholder-grPmrg dxAvXx"></div></div></div></div><div data-testid="RowWrapper" class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd RowWrapper-UmqTg iUEiRd HEhan full-bleed-ad row-mid-content-ad"><div class="StickyMidContentAdWrapper-fSBzwl drzyIa ad-stickymidcontent"><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--mid-content should-hold-space"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--mid-content" data-node-id="1g7uy"></div></div></div></div><div class="GridWrapper-cAzTTK kHBDeH grid grid-margins grid-items-2 ArticlePageChunksGrid-hfxaau eSqXkM grid-layout--adrail narrow wide-adrail"><div class="GridItem-buujkM stRKV grid--item grid-layout__content"><div class="BodyWrapper-kufPGa jVpVTh body body__container article__body" data-journey-hook="client-content" data-testid="BodyWrapper"><div class="body__inner-container"><figure class="AssetEmbedWrapper-eVDQiB byBkf asset-embed"><div class="AssetEmbedAssetContainer-eJxoAx dBHGoQ asset-embed__asset-container"><span class="SpanWrapper-umhxW kGxnNB responsive-asset AssetEmbedResponsiveAsset-cXBNxi eCxVQK asset-embed__responsive-asset"><picture class="ResponsiveImagePicture-cWuUZO dUOtEa AssetEmbedResponsiveAsset-cXBNxi eCxVQK asset-embed__responsive-asset responsive-image"><noscript><img alt="Image may contain Building Factory Human Person and Brewery" class="ResponsiveImageContainer-eybHBd fptoWY responsive-image__image" src="https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_1600%2Cc_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg" srcSet="https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_120,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 120w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_240,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 240w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_320,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 320w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_640,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 640w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_960,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 960w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_1280,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 1280w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_1600,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 1600w" sizes="100vw"/></noscript></picture></span></div><div class="CaptionWrapper-jSZdqE ebtvos caption AssetEmbedCaption-fNQBPI fmQnYP asset-embed__caption"><span class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ CaptionText-bHjzlu iUEiRd fSbQGS iXWezO caption__text"><p>Mr. Tuna on the job at Goodfire Brewing Co.</p>
</span><span class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ CaptionCredit-ejegDm iUEiRd eDVoPq fNaHcW caption__credit">Elizabeth Cecil</span></div></figure><ol start="14"><li><p>Don’t skip the city’s trailblazers. When I was in college in nearby Lewiston a couple decades ago, a big night out with the visiting parents meant dinner at <a data-offer-url="http://www.forestreet.biz/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;http://www.forestreet.biz/&quot;}" href="http://www.forestreet.biz/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Fore Street</a>, which is still going strong. Add the reinvented <a data-offer-url="http://www.hugos.net/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;http://www.hugos.net/&quot;}" href="http://www.hugos.net/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Hugo’s</a> and the locals’ beloved <a data-offer-url="https://backbaygrill.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://backbaygrill.com/&quot;}" href="https://backbaygrill.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Back Bay Grill</a> to the classics list.</p></li><li><p>Ask yourself: What is <a data-offer-url="https://tentenpieportland.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://tentenpieportland.com/&quot;}" href="https://tentenpieportland.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Ten Ten Pié</a>? A French bakery? Japanese market? Bento box cafe? It doesn’t matter—I’m a fan of baker Atsuko Fujimoto (that rhubarb tart!) and Markos Miller’s eclectic general store, whatever it is.</p></li><li><p>Leave town! Biddeford is the best reason to drive 18 miles south. It’s home to one of the country’s best cookbook stores, <a data-offer-url="https://www.rabelaisbooks.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.rabelaisbooks.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.rabelaisbooks.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Rabelais</a> (say hello to Don and Sam for me) and upstarts <a data-offer-url="https://www.instagram.com/littlesprucebakingco/?hl=en" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.instagram.com/littlesprucebakingco/?hl=en&quot;}" href="https://www.instagram.com/littlesprucebakingco/?hl=en" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Little Spruce Baking Co.</a> and <a data-offer-url="https://www.eldamaine.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.eldamaine.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.eldamaine.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Elda</a> restaurant. It’s also home to the Single. Best. Diner. On. The. Planet. <a data-offer-url="http://www.palacedinerme.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;http://www.palacedinerme.com/&quot;}" href="http://www.palacedinerme.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Palace Diner</a>. The flapjacks are towering, the burger is smashed and crunchy, and the tuna salad sandwich is quickly becoming a Maine icon.</p></li></ol></div></div></div><div class="GridItem-buujkM fVLMby grid--item grid-layout__aside"><div class="StickyBoxWrapper-jfYBuk jxBcTH sticky-box"><div class="StickyBoxPrimary-dzWDWL cdhYoN sticky-box__primary"><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--rail"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--rail" data-node-id="0gmlg"></div></div><div class="ConsumerMarketingUnitThemedWrapper-iUTMTf jssHut consumer-marketing-unit consumer-marketing-unit--display-rail" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true"><div class="consumer-marketing-unit__slot consumer-marketing-unit__slot--display-rail"></div><div class="journey-unit"></div></div><div data-attr-viewport-monitor="" class="RecircMostPopularWrapper-bRuGTi nZGkR recirc-most-popular-wrapper viewport-monitor-anchor"></div></div><div class="StickyBoxPlaceholder-grPmrg dxAvXx"></div></div></div></div><div data-testid="RowWrapper" class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd RowWrapper-UmqTg iUEiRd HEhan full-bleed-ad row-mid-content-ad"><div class="StickyMidContentAdWrapper-fSBzwl drzyIa ad-stickymidcontent"><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--mid-content should-hold-space"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--mid-content" data-node-id="ccu78w"></div></div></div></div><div class="GridWrapper-cAzTTK kHBDeH grid grid-margins grid-items-2 ArticlePageChunksGrid-hfxaau eSqXkM grid-layout--adrail narrow wide-adrail"><div class="GridItem-buujkM stRKV grid--item grid-layout__content"><div class="BodyWrapper-kufPGa jVpVTh body body__container article__body" data-journey-hook="client-content" data-testid="BodyWrapper"><div class="body__inner-container"><figure class="AssetEmbedWrapper-eVDQiB byBkf asset-embed"><div class="AssetEmbedAssetContainer-eJxoAx dBHGoQ asset-embed__asset-container"><span class="SpanWrapper-umhxW kGxnNB responsive-asset AssetEmbedResponsiveAsset-cXBNxi eCxVQK asset-embed__responsive-asset"><picture class="ResponsiveImagePicture-cWuUZO dUOtEa AssetEmbedResponsiveAsset-cXBNxi eCxVQK asset-embed__responsive-asset responsive-image"><noscript><img alt="This image may contain Food" class="ResponsiveImageContainer-eybHBd fptoWY responsive-image__image" src="https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_1600%2Cc_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg" srcSet="https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_120,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 120w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_240,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 240w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_320,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 320w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_640,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 640w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_960,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 960w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_1280,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 1280w, https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_1600,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 1600w" sizes="100vw"/></noscript></picture></span></div><div class="CaptionWrapper-jSZdqE ebtvos caption AssetEmbedCaption-fNQBPI fmQnYP asset-embed__caption"><span class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ CaptionText-bHjzlu iUEiRd fSbQGS iXWezO caption__text"><p>All the pastries at Belleville</p>
</span><span class="BaseWrap-sc-gjQpdd BaseText-ewhhUZ CaptionCredit-ejegDm iUEiRd eDVoPq fNaHcW caption__credit">Elizabeth Cecil</span></div></figure><ol start="17"><li><p>Carbo-load at <a data-offer-url="https://blvl.me/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://blvl.me/&quot;}" href="https://blvl.me/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Belleville</a>, which is putting out the city’s best and butteriest croissants. Arrive at 11:30 a.m. sharp—that’s when the shop’s other signature dish, <a href="https://www.bonappetit.com/story/regional-pizza-styles">Roman-style pizza al taglio</a>, is pulled from the oven with toppings like fig and rosemary or shiitake and Gruyère. They also play Rush!</p></li><li><p>Discover my perfect hangout. Thanks to a tip from Kazeem Lawal of <a data-offer-url="https://www.portlandtradingco.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.portlandtradingco.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.portlandtradingco.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Portland Trading Co.</a> (he plays the best vinyl) just up the street, I found out about a tiny pub called <a data-offer-url="https://www.facebook.com/portlandmaine.MAPS/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.facebook.com/portlandmaine.MAPS/&quot;}" href="https://www.facebook.com/portlandmaine.MAPS/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Maps</a> with local craft beers, vinyl, and vintage, yes, maps. When lobster-roll-seeking tourists of the Old Port are too much, this is your safe place.</p></li><li><p>Make room for Middle Eastern–inspired <a data-offer-url="https://www.baharatmaine.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.baharatmaine.com/&quot;}" href="https://www.baharatmaine.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Baharat</a>’s Turkish crab dip with house-made chips and takoyaki and okonomiyaki from Japanese comfort food spot <a data-offer-url="https://mamifoodtruck.com/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://mamifoodtruck.com/&quot;}" href="https://mamifoodtruck.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Mami</a>, which prove that you can go from great food truck to even better brick-and-mortar.</p></li><li><p>Pull up a stool at tried-and-true <a data-offer-url="http://www.dimillos.com/restaurant/" class="external-link" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;http://www.dimillos.com/restaurant/&quot;}" href="http://www.dimillos.com/restaurant/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">DiMillo’s on the Water</a> for the old-school wood bar, prime people-watching, and bacon-wrapped scallops.</p></li></ol><p><em>Check back Tuesday, August 14, to find out if Rose Foods or Drifters Wife made the Hot 10.</em></p></div></div></div><div class="GridItem-buujkM fVLMby grid--item grid-layout__aside"><div class="StickyBoxWrapper-jfYBuk jxBcTH sticky-box"><div class="StickyBoxPrimary-dzWDWL cdhYoN sticky-box__primary"><div class="AdWrapper-dQtivb fZrssQ ad ad--rail"><div class="ad__slot ad__slot--rail" data-node-id="t8fbad"></div></div><div class="ConsumerMarketingUnitThemedWrapper-iUTMTf jssHut consumer-marketing-unit consumer-marketing-unit--display-rail" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true"><div class="consumer-marketing-unit__slot consumer-marketing-unit__slot--display-rail"></div><div class="journey-unit"></div></div></div><div class="StickyBoxPlaceholder-grPmrg dxAvXx"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="GridWrapper-cAzTTK kHBDeH grid grid-margins grid-items-2 PaywallInlineBarrierWithWrapperGrid-fyrGfS kLQIUk grid-layout--adrail narrow wide-adrail"><div class="GridItem-buujkM stRKV grid--item grid-layout__